  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q001098.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(1) For Ninĝirsu , Enlil’s warrior , En-metena , ruler of Lagaš , child of En-ana-tum , ruler of Lagaš , built the sanctuary of Dugru . He built the Ahuš , the temple that is looked upon with favour , for him ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001098.14",
      "line_range": "14",
      "translation": "(14) For Nanše , he built the E-engur in Zulum , and built her high temple for her . He built the E-šage-pada ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001098.21",
      "line_range": "21",
      "translation": "(21) For Enlil , he built the E-adda in Imsaĝ ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001098.24",
      "line_range": "24",
      "translation": "(25) He built the temple of Ĝatumdug ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001098.26",
      "line_range": "26",
      "translation": "(27) He built the temple of Ninmah , the high temple of Tirkug ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001098.30",
      "line_range": "30",
      "translation": "(31) For Lugal-Uruba , he built his great temple in Urub ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001098.34",
      "line_range": "34",
      "translation": "(35) For Enki , king of Eridug , he built the Abzu-pasira ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001098.37",
      "line_range": "37",
      "translation": "(38) For Ninĝirsu , he built the Antasura , the temple whose fearsome radiance covers all the lands ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001098.41",
      "line_range": "41",
      "translation": "(42) The personal god of En-metena , the builder of the Antasura , is Šul-MUŠxPA ."
    }
  ],
